Home > Music > Remy Ma Points Out That "ShETHER" Is Charting Higher Than Nicki Minaj's "Make Love" Remy Ma Points Out That "ShETHER" Is Charting Higher Than Nicki Minaj's "Make Love" 0 0 Posted by Trevor Smith , Feb 27, 2017 at 07:05pm It's at #9 on the iTunes rap charts. 
So far Nicki Minaj 's only response to Remy Ma 's "ShETHER" diss track was posting the lackluster sales of Remy Ma's Fat Joe collaborative album Plata O Plomo. Despite slow sales of the album, the diss track has now earned Remy a new chart-related flex. The rapper shared a screencap of the iTunes rap charts on Twitter today, revealing that her "Ether" freestyle was not only charting at #9, but was one spot ahead of Gucci Mane and Nicki Minaj's "Make Love," one of the records that is said to have triggered Remy's attack.
